The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Binny right choice, says Sourav
                                                   Binny right choice, says Sourav
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Bengals new coach Roger Binny received a thumbs-up from Sourav Ganguly, on Sunday, who described the former India allrounder as the right choice for the team.         
	Sourav, who was speaking after participating in a benefit football match for the Aila victims organised by West Bengal Motion Pictures Artists Forum at the Barasat Stadium, said: Binny is the right choice as Bengal coach. I have known him for a long time and know that he will be very good for the team.         
	The match, in which the Film Stars XI beat the Television Stars XI via penalty shootout after a 1-1 draw at the end of regulation time, attracted more than 15000 people.         
	Sourav was the only successful scorer in the shootout for the Television Stars XI. It was nice to play football after a long time Also it was for a noble cause. So, I thoroughly enjoyed the experience, said Sourav.                                                                                                                       
